  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">213317_DEC Phase 2 - Cyclone Idai Response Mozambique</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project will focus on two sectors to support lifesaving interventions. These include WASH and Protection for families transitioning home. 
 
 
 
 Protection: The project will focus heavily on protection interventions for all vulnerable individuals and will support protection mainstreaming and referral system strengthening by working with the existing Child Protection Committees (CPC) established in phase 1. Through training new volunteers, they will help with the identification of children and families in need of support, such as CP related case management, and refer them to the relevant government structures. This will reduce the chances of harmful practices like child marriage, child labour, trafficking and transactional sex through community dialogues and awareness raising. 
 
 
 
 WASH: The DEC funding will complement a number of other projects in Buzi and Nhamatanda. 
 
 Through assessments and monitoring WV has identified a need for restoration of a number of water points in Buzi and Nhamatanda to decrease the risk of cholera and other waterborne disease outbreaks as IDPs return home. With regards to WASH interventions WV will rehabilitate 5 water points under DEC funding, while working with water committees and hygiene promoters that will be identified and trained under UNICEF and ADH grants. Increased access to clean water is not a stand-alone intervention for reducing the risk of cholera and thus, WV will also work with the Hong Kong Government and ADH on HH latrine construction and hygiene messaging in order to ensure complementary programming.</narrative>
  </description>
